   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Fifty-four TWO WAYS Scripture: Jer 21:8 Man s opportunity Man s opportunity comes from God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God has set two ways before man: the way of life and the way of death.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In the beginning, after God made man, He put man in front of life the tree of life and death the tree of the knowledge of good and evil .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>God let man choose life or death.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Both ways are opportunities given by God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The choice and the decision are up to man.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Man s free will to choose God set two ways before man because God gave man a free will.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The fact that man is given a free will is a proof that God honors man, and also that man is the highest creature.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>God let man choose either life or death according to man s free will.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The results of these two ways The way of life leads to eternal life, which includes God s life, the eternal peace and blessing, and the heavenly joy.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The way of death leads to eternal death, which includes the elements of Satan, eternal suffering, and punishment in the lake of fire.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>How to choose the way of life Acknowledge that you are already on the way of death the way you have been treading is a way of death.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Turn from the way of death.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Repent and confess your sins.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Believe that Christ is the life and the way.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Only He can give man life, and only He can lead man to the way of life.</S>
   </TEXT>
